Title: Description
RG300: Dataset proposed in the paper Vanhoucke, M., Coelho, J., and Batselier, J. (2016). An overview of project data for integrated project management and control. Journal of Modern Project Management, 3(2):6–21.

Title: # Reference
RG300: Demeulemeester, E. and Herroelen, W. (1992). A branch-and-bound procedure for the multiple resource-constrained project scheduling problem. Management Science, 38:1803-1818.

Title: # Hardware / software
RG300: Stevin Supercomputer Infrastructure, C++, compiler intel/2017.02, Linux

Title: # Reference
RG300: Klein, R. and Scholl, A. (1999). Computing lower bounds by destructive improvement: An application to resource-constrained project scheduling. European Journal of Operational Research, 112:322?346

Title: # Reference
RG300: Debels, D. and Vanhoucke, M. (2007). A decomposition-based genetic algorithm for the resource-constrained project scheduling problems. Operations Research, 55:457-469.

Title: # Hardware / software
RG300: Stevin Supercomputer Infrastructure, C++, compiler intel/2017.02, Linux

Title: # Stop criteria
RG300: cumulated results from several runs, on open instances only. Maximal run: 100 runs x 500k schedules

Title: # Reference
RG300: Coelho, Jose, Vanhoucke, Mario. 2018. "An exact composite lower bound strategy for the resource-constrained project scheduling problem", Computers & Operations Research 93, 1: 135 - 150. doi: 10.1016/j.cor.2018.01.017

Title: # Hardware / software
RG300: STEVIN HPC-UGent infrastructure, C++, compiler intel/2017.02, Linux

Title: # Stop criteria
RG300: Result of several runs done in the paper, maximal time of 1 hour, UBs, LBs and OPT solutions.

Title: # Reference
RG300: Laborie, P. (2023). Fast lower-bounds for scheduling problems in LocalSolver. ROADEF 2023 (in French)

Title: # Hardware/software
RG300: Intel i7-12700H, 2,3 GHz, 14 cores, 20 threads, 32Go RAM
